{
  "ProofStructure": [
    {
      "meaning": [
        "A sequence $x_1, x_2, \\ldots$",
        "$x_1 = 1$",
        "$x_{2k} = -x_k$",
        "$x_{2k-1} = (-1)^{k+1} x_k$",
        "for all $k \\geq 1$"
      ],
      "symbol": "x",
      "type": "Define"
    },
    {
      "proposition": [
        "$x_1 + x_2 + \\cdots + x_n \\geq 0$ for all $n \\geq 1$"
      ],
      "type": "Show"
    },
    {
      "comment": "We start with some observations.",
      "type": "Hint"
    },
    {
      "proposition": [
        "from the definition of $x_i$ it follows that for each positive integer $k$ we have $x_{4k-3} = x_{2k-1} = -x_{4k-2}$ and $x_{4k-1} = x_{4k} = -x_{2k} = x_k$."
      ],
      "reasons": [
        "from the definition of $x_i$"
      ],
      "type": "Have"
    },
    {
      "meaning": [
        "$S_n = \\sum_{i=1}^n x_i$"
      ],
      "symbol": "$S_n$",
      "type": "Define"
    },
    {
      "proposition": [
        "$S_{4k} = \\sum_{i=1}^k ((x_{4k-3} + x_{4k-2}) + (x_{4k-1} + x_{4k})) = \\sum_{i=1}^k (0 + 2x_k) = 2S_k$"
      ],
      "reasons": [],
      "type": "Have"
    },
    {
      "proposition": [
        "$S_{4k+2} = S_{4k} + (x_{4k+1} + x_{4k+2}) = S_{4k}$"
      ],
      "reasons": [],
      "type": "Have"
    },
    {
      "proposition": [
        "$S_n = \\sum_{i=1}^n x_i \\equiv \\sum_{i=1}^n 1 = n \\ (\\text{mod} \\ 2)$"
      ],
      "reasons": [],
      "type": "Have"
    },
    {
      "comment": "Now we prove by induction on $k$ that $S_i \\geq 0$ for all $i \\leq 4k$.",
      "type": "Hint"
    },
    {
      "proposition": [
        "The base case is valid since $x_1 = x_3 = x_4 = 1, x_2 = -1$."
      ],
      "reasons": [],
      "type": "Have"
    },
    {
      "comment": "For the induction step",
      "type": "Hint"
    },
    {
      "assumption": [
        "$S_i \\geq 0$ for all $i \\leq 4k$"
      ],
      "type": "Assume"
    },
    {
      "proposition": [
        "$S_{4k+4} = 2S_{k+1} \\geq 0, \\quad S_{4k+2} = S_{4k} \\geq 0, \\quad S_{4k+3} = S_{4k+2} + x_{4k+3} = \\frac{S_{4k+2} + S_{4k+4}}{2} \\geq 0.$"
      ],
      "reasons": [
        "Using the relations (1)-(3)"
      ],
      "type": "Have"
    },
    {
      "proposition": [
        "$S_{4k+1} \\geq 0$"
      ],
      "type": "Show"
    },
    {
      "assumption": [
        "$k$ is odd"
      ],
      "type": "Assume"
    },
    {
      "proposition": [
        "$S_{4k} = 2S_k \\geq 0$; since $k$ is odd, $S_k$ is odd as well, so we have $S_{4k} \\geq 2$ and hence $S_{4k+1} = S_{4k} + x_{4k+1} \\geq 1$."
      ],
      "reasons": [],
      "type": "Have"
    },
    {
      "assumption": [
        "$k$ is even"
      ],
      "type": "Assume"
    },
    {
      "proposition": [
        "$x_{4k+1} = x_{2k+1} = x_{k+1}$"
      ],
      "reasons": [],
      "type": "Have"
    },
    {
      "proposition": [
        "$S_{4k+1} = S_{4k} + x_{4k+1} = 2S_k + x_{k+1} = S_k + S_{k+1} \\geq 0$"
      ],
      "reasons": [],
      "type": "Have"
    },
    {
      "comment": "The step is proved.",
      "type": "Hint"
    }
  ]
}